            "cover": "/static/media/mirage_cover.jpg",
            "navigation": "/static/media/mirage_navigation.jpg",
            "content": {
                "title": "Think Mirage",
                "excerpt": "What place does man want to give to the technology in his life? Mirage lets you think about it.",
                "description": "Mirage is an interactive short movie about transhumanism and the place that human gives to the technology in his life. It was my graduation project at Gobelins, l'École de l'Image, Paris – France. Online soon.",
                "preview": [
                    {
                        "type": "video",
                        "content": {
                            "poster": "/static/media/mirage_poster-1.jpg",
                            "src": "/static/media/mirage_screen-1.mp4"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "video",
                        "content": {
                            "poster": "/static/media/mirage_poster-2.jpg",
                            "src": "/static/media/mirage_screen-2.mp4"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "image",
                        "content": {
                            "src": "/static/media/mirage_poster-3.jpg"
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "details": [
                    {
                        "title": "Thinking",
                        "text": "We thought that a lot of people want to change the world. Perhaps to avoid the inevitable scenario that leads man to death. With transhumanism, we suggest a prospective evolution of humanity and ask the user what place does he want to give to the technology in his life?"
                    },
                    {
                        "title": "Story",
                        "text": "Edward loves his wife and his kid. He's afraid of anything that might happen to them. So he dreams of himself as being stronger, sharper and more aware of the world around him, to protect them. He dreams of IO, an artificial intelligence in his brain that can analyze a situation much faster than him and even suggests the best things he may chose."
                    },
                    {
                        "title": "Installation",
                        "text": "The experience will be available online soon. But, we thought that the subject and our purpose could interested people in a different way. That is why we built a physical installation. It's consists of a sensitive glass display surrounded by a wooden structure. We use a combination of IR leds, IR camera and video projector to achieve this performance."
                    }
                ],
